  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX spot at 6781.84 sitting right at the GEX flip strike of 6780, dealers are positioned at the critical inflection point where they transition from buying dips below to selling rallies above. The massive positive gamma wall at 6780 (29.7B) combined with the wall_break and gex_surge events indicates dealers just shifted into heavy selling mode as spot pushed through this level, creating significant resistance. The dense cluster of positive gamma walls from 6780-6800 (all 20B+) will act as a ceiling, with dealers aggressively selling any move higher to hedge their long gamma positions.\n\nKey levels: 6770 (max negative gamma - dealer buying support) below and the 6780-6800 wall cluster (dealer selling zone) above.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get capped near current levels with dealers selling any bounce toward 6800.",
